<section id="application">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-lg-12 text-center">
        <h2 class="section-heading text-faded">
          2019 APPLICATION
        </h2>
        <hr class="primary">
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="container">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-md-12 text-center">
        <p class="text-faded">
          please see the homepage for details on festival activities, the application, and logistics.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <br />
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-md-12 text-center">
        <p class="text-faded">
          <h3>important dates</h3>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <br />
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-md-8 col-md-offset-2 text-center">
        <ul style="list-style: none;">
          <li>
            <p class="text-faded">
              applications due on sunday, oct 28, by 11:59 pm (est)
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p class="text-faded">
              acceptance (or not) sent via e-mail november 7th
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p class="text-faded">
              confirmation of attendance due nov 21
            </p>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="container" id="collapseExample"> 
    <br />
    <hr />
    <%= form_for(@coincidentTroi, :html => {:class => "form-inline"} ) do |f| %>
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-6">
          <h3>
            personal info (required)
          </h3>
          <p class="text-faded">
            please let us know who you are! our main means of contact will be e-mail, so please check it (and your spam folder) regularly.
          </p>
          <%= f.label :name, 'name', class: 'fugu-width' %>
          <%= f.text_field :name, class: 'form-control', :required => true %>
          <br />

          <%= f.label :email, 'email', class: 'fugu-width m-5-top' %>
          <%= f.text_field :email, class: 'form-control m-5-top', :required => true %>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-6">
          <h3>
            &nbsp;
          </h3>
          <%= f.label :birthday, 'birthday', :required => true, class: 'fugu-width m-5-top' %>
          <%= f.date_field :birthday, class: 'form-control m-5-top', :required => true %>
          <br />
          <%= f.label :address, 'address', :required => true, class: 'fugu-width m-5-top' %>
          <%= f.text_area :address, class: 'form-control m-5-top', :required => true %>
        </div>
      </div>
      <br />
      <hr />
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-6">
          <h3>
            portfolio
          </h3>
          <p class="text-faded">
            *all documents should be linked to via resources like dropbox and google drive. make sure the documents are accessible to us to view.*
          </p>

          <p class="text-faded">
            you may provide 1 - 3 work samples, in whatever form/format you feel best represents you. to note: we only require 1 work sample, and the number of work samples you submit will not negatively affect application.
          </p>
          <%= f.label :link1, 'work sample 1, link (required)', class: ' m-5-top', :required => true %>
          <%= f.text_field :link1, class: 'form-control', :required => true %>
          <br />
          <%= f.label :link2, 'work sample 2, link (optional)', class: ' m-5-top'  %>
          <%= f.text_field :link2, class: 'form-control m-5-top' %>
          <br />
          <%= f.label :link3, 'work sample 3, link (optional)', class: ' m-5-top'  %>
          <%= f.text_field :link3, class: 'form-control m-5-top' %>
          <br />
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-6">
          <div class="hidden-xs hidden-sm">
            <h3>
              &nbsp;
            </h3>
          </div>
          <%= f.label :website, "website (optional)" %>
          <%= f.text_field :website, class: 'form-control' %>
          <br />
          <p class="text-faded">
            
          </p>
          <%= f.label :tell_us, "please tell us about yourself: what have you been up to? what are you interested in? anything you want us to know?" %>
          <%= f.text_area :tell_us, class: 'form-control' %>
          <p class="text-faded">
          </p>
          <%= f.label :why_ams_you, "lastly, let us know why are you interested in the festival? (can be brief)" %>
          <%= f.text_area :why_ams_you, class: 'form-control' %>
        </div>
      </div>
      <br />
      <hr />
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-6">
          <h3>
            proposal
          </h3>
          <p class="text-faded">
            what is a recent concept-of-interest for you? could you briefly describe your engagement with it and provide us, if possible, a passage, essay, artwork, video, or otherwise that articulate it well. (we hope to fold the guest artist concepts-of-interest into our daily discussions).
          </p>
          <p class="text-faded">
            this year, we will be dealing with conversation as artistic labor, mapping as praxis, nomadic movement, and complicity as a mode of critical exchange between others. these are intended to be in service of collectively developing an ethic (or tactics) that is durable, yet malleable - something available for further and future use. part of this includes proposing various activity-pieces to occur during the festival. 
          </p>
          <p class="text-faded">
            what would you propose for an activity (one or several)? describe it and why you think it is interesting/significant both to our future group/social operations at the festival and your work. this, of course, is not binding, and we donâ€™t expect it to (but it might) be the activity you offer at the festival.
          </p>

        </div>
        <div class="col-md-6">
          <h3>
            &nbsp;
          </h3>
          <%= f.label :link_to_prompt, 'link to your response to the prompt', :required => true, class: ' m-5-top' %>
          <%= f.text_field :link_to_prompt, class: 'form-control form2', :required => true %>

          <br />
          <br />
          <%= f.submit 'SUBMIT APPLICATION', class: 'btn btn-secondary btn-fugu' %>
        </div>
      </div>
    <% end %>
  </div>
</section>